'''Gynecologic cytology''', also '''Gynecologic cytology''', is a field of [[pathology]] concerned with the investigation of disorders of the female [[genital tract]].  

The most common investigation in this field is the [[Pap test]], which is used to [[screening (medicine)|screen]] for potentially precancerous lesions of the [[cervix]].  Cytology can also be used to investigate disorders of the [[ovary|ovaries]], [[uterus]], [[vagina]] and [[vulva]].

